WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.480
[Amit Varma]: Here's a thought experiment I want you to think about and at the end of that

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:12.440
[Amit Varma]: experiment is a question. When I ask you that question I'd like you to pause this

00:00:12.440 --> 00:00:17.040
[Amit Varma]: podcast for a moment and take a stab at answering it. Imagine that you meet your

00:00:17.040 --> 00:00:21.160
[Amit Varma]: future self in a zoom call that somehow travels through time. You are allowed to

00:00:21.160 --> 00:00:27.000
[Amit Varma]: ask this future version of you one question. How should I live my life? What

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:31.880
[Amit Varma]: answer does your future self give? That's my question to you. What advice does your

00:00:31.880 --> 00:00:36.360
[Amit Varma]: future self give you when it comes to living your life? Pause and answer this

00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:42.920
[Amit Varma]: for me. Well here's my answer. My future self tells me two words. Pay attention.

00:00:42.920 --> 00:00:46.120
[Amit Varma]: When I think about the way I live my life that's one thing I don't do enough

00:00:46.120 --> 00:00:50.600
[Amit Varma]: of. That's one thing all of us don't do enough of. We spend time living in the

00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:54.680
[Amit Varma]: past or the future and not enough in the present and when we are in the present

00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:58.920
[Amit Varma]: we are not paying attention. We are always distracted, always absent. Think

00:00:58.920 --> 00:01:02.360
[Amit Varma]: about the modern marriage for example. What is the modern marriage? Two people

00:01:02.360 --> 00:01:06.880
[Amit Varma]: side-by-side in their bed, lights off, their face illuminated by the blue glow

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:10.960
[Amit Varma]: from the screen in front of them. What is the modern family? Maybe together

00:01:10.960 --> 00:01:15.360
[Amit Varma]: sometimes physically but always alone together. You sit with your loved ones

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:19.360
[Amit Varma]: and stare into your phone. You sit at a cafe and never once look around you. You

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:23.380
[Amit Varma]: find yourself in a beautiful place and you take pictures one after another, even

00:01:23.380 --> 00:01:28.080
[Amit Varma]: high-definition video so that you don't lose a moment and in doing so you don't

00:01:28.080 --> 00:01:32.400
[Amit Varma]: even get to live the moment. One thing I'd like to do more of in the time that

00:01:32.400 --> 00:01:36.960
[Amit Varma]: I have left is be present in the moment. Pay attention. Pay attention to all the

00:01:36.960 --> 00:01:40.800
[Amit Varma]: sensations around me. Pay attention to the people around me who might not be

00:01:40.800 --> 00:01:44.380
[Amit Varma]: there tomorrow when it will be too late and one of the things I should pay

00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:48.960
[Amit Varma]: attention to is my own body. What is it telling me? What am I doing wrong? And

00:01:48.960 --> 00:01:54.000
[Amit Varma]: also what food am I putting into it? I mean this is my body. The soul only

00:01:54.000 --> 00:02:00.240
[Amit Varma]: exists as a metaphor. My body is all of me. So what I put into it should be a big

00:02:00.240 --> 00:02:05.160
[Amit Varma]: big deal. Is it a big deal for you? How deeply have you thought about the food

00:02:05.160 --> 00:02:07.640
[Amit Varma]: that you eat?

