[Amit Varma]: willingness to work hard and a clear idea of what you need to do to refine

01:11:50.880 --> 01:11:57.640
[Amit Varma]: your skills I can help you. Welcome back to the seen and the unseen I'm chatting

01:11:57.640 --> 01:12:02.000
[Amit Varma]: with Nandita Iyer about her superb book everyday superfoods and about a very

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:05.680
[Amit Varma]: interesting life and her journey into learning more about food but before we

01:12:05.680 --> 01:12:10.920
[Amit Varma]: actually get to the food so to say let's kind of go back to the way your life is

01:12:10.920 --> 01:12:15.520
[Amit Varma]: unwinding after you have you know left medicine because of politics as it were

01:12:15.520 --> 01:12:18.840
[Amit Varma]: at this point in time what is your conception of yourself what do you want

01:12:18.840 --> 01:12:24.560
[Amit Varma]: to do what are the you know parts that you're thinking about so definitely I

01:12:24.560 --> 01:12:29.600
[Guest]: wasn't a kind of I was in a crossroad and I didn't I didn't really know what

01:12:29.600 --> 01:12:36.240
[Guest]: my next steps would be and one option definitely was to maybe start like a

01:12:36.240 --> 01:12:41.800
[Guest]: general practitioner kind of a practice because there was always a huge emphasis

01:12:41.800 --> 01:12:46.760
[Guest]: on being a super specialist and stuff but even in those days that whole GP

01:12:46.760 --> 01:12:50.880
[Guest]: concept was dying down to have like a friendly neighborhood doctor who can

01:12:50.880 --> 01:12:55.360
[Guest]: take care of all your basic problems and I thought I'm okay for that level of

01:12:55.360 --> 01:13:01.600
[Guest]: stress and I can still handle that that was one thing on my mind and the second

01:13:01.600 --> 01:13:06.840
[Guest]: thing was that what else can I do with now that I have my medical degree can I

01:13:06.840 --> 01:13:13.480
[Guest]: study like an MBA or can I do some other further studies which will open up some

01:13:13.480 --> 01:13:17.880
[Guest]: more paths to me other than just being a clinical doctor while I was thinking

01:13:17.880 --> 01:13:23.080
[Guest]: about these things I got a job opportunity in health insurance related

01:13:23.080 --> 01:13:27.640
[Guest]: company where they were looking for doctors to understand certain aspects of

01:13:27.640 --> 01:13:31.960
[Guest]: the claims and you know because a general person will not really know okay

01:13:31.960 --> 01:13:36.320
[Guest]: this was the ailment and all this was done for this ailment so you need

01:13:36.320 --> 01:13:40.760
[Guest]: someone to actually know what was actually required and what were not

01:13:40.760 --> 01:13:45.840
[Guest]: required so to sort out those kind of things and because I didn't want to sit

01:13:45.840 --> 01:13:49.800
[Guest]: at home for a single day and at this point an idle mind would have definitely

01:13:49.800 --> 01:13:54.320
[Guest]: been a devil's workshop with all the stuff that I had experienced and gone

01:13:54.320 --> 01:13:58.400
[Guest]: through and come out of and I think that would have been the right time to see a

01:13:58.400 --> 01:14:02.280
[Guest]: therapist or something but that was out of question I didn't even know about you

01:14:02.280 --> 01:14:06.720
[Guest]: know those kind of terminologies and even having studied medicine I didn't

01:14:06.720 --> 01:14:11.360
[Guest]: even think of it as an option at that point of time there was this opening in

01:14:11.360 --> 01:14:15.600
[Guest]: a health insurance related company and I just went and I took on that job and it

01:14:15.600 --> 01:14:20.400
[Guest]: would keep my mind occupied and I said like while I do this I can understand if

01:14:20.400 --> 01:14:25.520
[Guest]: this is something to my liking or I can see what else to do and I worked in that

01:14:25.520 --> 01:14:31.040
[Guest]: field for two to three years and but again I've always been like a very

01:14:31.040 --> 01:14:36.280
[Guest]: creative person and I need some kind of creativity and some that that's the

01:14:36.280 --> 01:14:41.520
[Guest]: thing that gives me joy and here I was neither seeing patients and nor am I

01:14:41.520 --> 01:14:48.120
[Guest]: doing anything creative that makes me happy and I said this okay while I was

01:14:48.120 --> 01:14:53.000
[Guest]: getting some decent salary and stuff and I was not wasting my time at home I was

01:14:53.000 --> 01:14:59.320
[Guest]: not entirely satisfied with what I was doing it felt very dry and boring at

01:14:59.320 --> 01:15:03.940
[Guest]: this point I should also mention that I was a very early adopter into social

01:15:03.940 --> 01:15:08.400
[Guest]: media even before the term social media existed so there was this networking

01:15:08.400 --> 01:15:13.160
[Guest]: site called the rise business networking early on I didn't know what it was but I

01:15:13.160 --> 01:15:17.920
[Guest]: just made an account for myself and I was connecting with a lot of people

01:15:17.920 --> 01:15:23.280
[Guest]: around also because I was not in touch with my own classmates and you know five

01:15:23.280 --> 01:15:26.720
[Guest]: and a half years of doing medicine leaves you with no friends no nothing in

01:15:26.720 --> 01:15:32.160
[Guest]: your social life and you don't know anybody so then I said okay let me join

01:15:32.160 --> 01:15:35.160
[Guest]: this I'll at least get to know people from other fields because you've been

01:15:35.160 --> 01:15:40.000
[Guest]: living in a literal blinkered existence for from the day you step into medical

01:15:40.000 --> 01:15:44.000
[Guest]: college you don't know what is happening in the outside world so I joined this

01:15:44.000 --> 01:15:48.440
[Guest]: website and I came across people from advertising from so many different I

01:15:48.440 --> 01:15:53.480
[Guest]: think Prem Panikkar and all I knew from that site early on because that same

01:15:53.480 --> 01:15:58.760
[Guest]: gang moves on to every new good platform everybody is on Twitter now so literally

01:15:58.760 --> 01:16:04.040
[Guest]: I know them for like 20 years I think so so I went on to that platform and I found

01:16:04.040 --> 01:16:07.120
[Guest]: out thanks to that I came to know that there is something called health care

01:16:07.120 --> 01:16:11.560
[Guest]: advertising which I would have not known otherwise and you know there's this

01:16:11.560 --> 01:16:16.160
[Guest]: certain law which says that once you have heard about something you tend to

01:16:16.160 --> 01:16:20.080
[Guest]: keep seeing similar things around you right I forget what's the name for that

01:16:20.080 --> 01:16:24.000
[Guest]: phenomenon immediately after I saw that in a couple of days there was this

01:16:24.000 --> 01:16:28.360
[Guest]: article in the Sunday supplement of Times of India about this new field

01:16:28.360 --> 01:16:31.760
[Guest]: called health care advertising and all I said wow I just came to know about this

01:16:31.760 --> 01:16:35.080
[Guest]: two days ago and now I'm reading about it in the newspaper I mean is this a

01:16:35.080 --> 01:16:41.480
[Guest]: sign maybe I can apply my medical knowledge I can write it is creative and

01:16:41.480 --> 01:16:46.840
[Guest]: it kind of seemed exciting to me at that point of time and I said but how on

01:16:46.840 --> 01:16:51.880
[Guest]: earth I've never given a job interview in my life I don't have any management

01:16:51.880 --> 01:16:55.160
[Guest]: degree I don't have any advertising background all I have is a medical

01:16:55.160 --> 01:17:00.120
[Guest]: degree what am I going to how am I going to get this and somehow through one of

01:17:00.120 --> 01:17:04.560
[Guest]: the contacts and drives I got the contact of the woman who was heading

01:17:04.560 --> 01:17:09.880
[Guest]: Ogilvy health care which is a branch of Ogilvy and Mathur a very leading ad

01:17:09.880 --> 01:17:17.000
[Guest]: agency which is all over the world and this was the Mumbai branch so I just you

01:17:17.000 --> 01:17:22.200
[Guest]: know some sometimes I have the spurt of confidence and drive I said let's do it

01:17:22.200 --> 01:17:27.440
[Guest]: worst case what will happen she'll say get lost at least it would not be for

01:17:27.440 --> 01:17:33.640
[Guest]: want of not trying so I just contacted her and I said I want to come and meet

01:17:33.640 --> 01:17:38.080
[Guest]: you can you give me like 15-20 minutes of your time and also these are the

01:17:38.080 --> 01:17:41.280
[Guest]: places where your doctor's degree sometimes helps because the minute they

01:17:41.280 --> 01:17:44.080
[Guest]: see a doctor's degree they think they can't be such a nonsense person they

01:17:44.080 --> 01:17:48.520
[Guest]: have some you know some substance in them and people don't refuse you when

01:17:48.520 --> 01:17:54.400
[Guest]: you request for a meeting like this so I went and met her and she heard me out

01:17:54.400 --> 01:17:57.960
[Guest]: and she said I said I want to be a part of this but to be honest I don't even

01:17:57.960 --> 01:18:02.640
[Guest]: know what are the available options for me but somehow I feel like I could fit

01:18:02.640 --> 01:18:07.840
[Guest]: in here I think I would feel that kind of creative fulfillment at place like

01:18:07.840 --> 01:18:11.960
[Guest]: this what she did was very interesting she gave me a project and said I'm

01:18:11.960 --> 01:18:16.440
[Guest]: giving you two weeks you do this project in whatever way I'm not going to give

01:18:16.440 --> 01:18:20.160
[Guest]: you any guidelines or how we work out here you will just figure it out with

01:18:20.160 --> 01:18:25.440
[Guest]: your own logic and you do this and you come back to me and I did it and I went

01:18:25.440 --> 01:18:29.320
[Guest]: back in two weeks and I got the job and she said okay so I joined a strategy

01:18:29.320 --> 01:18:33.640
[Guest]: planner so in healthcare advertising this was mainly for the pharma companies

01:18:33.640 --> 01:18:37.720
[Guest]: so these are the kind of brochures and literatures that the medical

01:18:37.720 --> 01:18:41.880
[Guest]: representatives take to the doctors and they tell them about these new drugs and

01:18:41.880 --> 01:18:47.360
[Guest]: but also there are the same drug is manufactured by five ten different

01:18:47.360 --> 01:18:51.920
[Guest]: companies so how do you gain some mind space in the doctor's head that he

01:18:51.920 --> 01:18:56.800
[Guest]: remembers your brand better maybe because you conveyed it in a better way

01:18:56.800 --> 01:19:02.280
[Guest]: or for whatever reason so that was the speciality of this field where you made

01:19:02.280 --> 01:19:06.200
[Guest]: a creative communication rather than just dry blah blah blah twice a day you

01:19:06.200 --> 01:19:10.040
[Guest]: give this is the milligram this is the side effect you know going beyond that

01:19:10.040 --> 01:19:15.600
[Guest]: and trying to catch some emotions and that's the typical Ogilvy way of doing

01:19:15.600 --> 01:19:19.480
[Guest]: things where everything has their own touch and their spin and they make

01:19:19.480 --> 01:19:23.080
[Guest]: anything and they can make fevicol interesting so you can imagine how it is

01:19:23.080 --> 01:19:31.160
[Guest]: so that's how I you know got the job and I really enjoyed it but there was one

01:19:31.160 --> 01:19:36.440
[Guest]: you know one drawback was that these guys are all like very late starters in

01:19:36.440 --> 01:19:42.520
[Guest]: the day and I'm a morning person I'll be there by 830 in the morning and people

01:19:42.520 --> 01:19:46.920
[Guest]: come in by 1231 and when I wanted to leave on time they'll say are a half day

01:19:46.920 --> 01:19:51.320
[Guest]: kind of you know because no one knows that you've been working from early and

01:19:51.320 --> 01:19:54.760
[Guest]: and that whole culture was very different for someone coming from a

01:19:54.760 --> 01:19:59.560
[Guest]: medical background it's very laid-back if there's a deadline for 5 p.m. 430 is

01:19:59.560 --> 01:20:03.720
[Guest]: when people will start working on something which would like make me very

01:20:03.720 --> 01:20:09.240
[Guest]: panicky because I I'm not although even I do my best when you know the deadline

01:20:09.240 --> 01:20:13.680
[Guest]: is closest but I'll not start my work half an hour before I have to submit it

01:20:13.680 --> 01:20:18.680
[Guest]: that is something that will drive me crazy out of you know anxiety that I've

01:20:18.680 --> 01:20:25.800
[Guest]: not started my work so I got used to that kind of lifestyle also where again

01:20:25.800 --> 01:20:31.280
[Guest]: all from different fields one somebody's in art somebody's a client servicing and

01:20:31.280 --> 01:20:35.840
[Guest]: I am here dealing like in middleman between the advertising and the pharma

01:20:35.840 --> 01:20:42.960
[Guest]: company so then by now I was in my late 20s after all these winding you know

01:20:42.960 --> 01:20:48.720
[Guest]: side paths that I had taken and I was chugging along and then I got married in

01:20:48.720 --> 01:20:55.880
[Guest]: my late 20s and at that time my husband had a job in the US and that was

01:20:55.880 --> 01:21:00.880
[Guest]: literally the first time I I think I traveled outside the country and I went

01:21:00.880 --> 01:21:05.640
[Guest]: to I went I went off to the East Coast with him after I got married and that

01:21:05.640 --> 01:21:11.360
[Guest]: was the first time in my life I was sitting at home 100% leisure nothing to

01:21:11.360 --> 01:21:18.040
[Guest]: do no deadlines and all my time is my own to do as I please and you know after

01:21:18.040 --> 01:21:22.280
[Guest]: I think after middle school like fifth standard sixth standard seventh standard

01:21:22.280 --> 01:21:28.840
[Guest]: this was the first time I was in truly zone where I had nothing to account for

01:21:28.840 --> 01:21:35.480
[Guest]: and I could just do my own thing and that is when the food bug bit me because

01:21:35.480 --> 01:21:41.200
[Guest]: I used to I was fascinated by the kind of channels that were on TV and I was

01:21:41.200 --> 01:21:44.560
[Guest]: even more fascinated that there was a channel to tell you what's going on on

01:21:44.560 --> 01:21:50.880
[Guest]: all the other channels and for someone who has only seen like Krishi Darshan and

01:21:50.880 --> 01:21:55.360
[Guest]: stuff back home because that's when my TV watching days also stopped after that

01:21:55.360 --> 01:21:59.400
[Guest]: there was no chance to watch TV and I was totally fascinated and there was a

01:21:59.400 --> 01:22:04.800
[Guest]: food network channel which was showing 24 by 7 food things on you know anytime

01:22:04.800 --> 01:22:08.120
[Guest]: if you couldn't get sleep or you were jet-lagged you just started the TV and

01:22:08.120 --> 01:22:12.840
[Guest]: you could watch like someone cooking and I found that like utterly fascinating

01:22:12.840 --> 01:22:17.240
[Guest]: and then all apartments they come with this built-in oven which again I was

01:22:17.240 --> 01:22:20.680
[Guest]: seeing for the first time I've never had an oven in my life so like it took me

01:22:20.680 --> 01:22:24.880
[Guest]: two days to even figure out how what is on what is off what because everyone

01:22:24.880 --> 01:22:29.440
[Guest]: just uses it as a storage to keep extra pots and pans so just took a while to

01:22:29.440 --> 01:22:33.420
[Guest]: figure that out and then all that inspiration from food TV plus the

01:22:33.420 --> 01:22:37.880
[Guest]: supermarkets with all the supplies and like so many things to buy which we

01:22:37.880 --> 01:22:43.720
[Guest]: didn't have and this was in the year 2004 even though we had supermarkets in

01:22:43.720 --> 01:22:48.120
[Guest]: India at that time that kind of variety even today you will not find right so

01:22:48.120 --> 01:22:53.360
[Guest]: all that put together I actually started cooking and experimenting and I would

01:22:53.360 --> 01:22:56.800
[Guest]: say experimenting because I really didn't know much about like even I didn't

01:22:56.800 --> 01:23:01.520
[Guest]: know the exact recipe for a sambar or a rasam or anything for that matter so I

01:23:01.520 --> 01:23:06.280
[Guest]: think all that inspiration put together is when I started cooking and

01:23:06.280 --> 01:23:10.400
[Guest]: experimenting and those days it's not like you had whatsapp so you could

01:23:10.400 --> 01:23:14.000
[Guest]: quickly call your mom and literally keep the stuff on the gas and say now tell me

01:23:14.000 --> 01:23:18.480
[Guest]: how do I make this so I started I would call her and I would start making notes

01:23:18.480 --> 01:23:23.520
[Guest]: and at least certain things that reminded me of home and the stuff food that I had

01:23:23.520 --> 01:23:29.200
[Guest]: enjoyed in my childhood I wanted to recreate that because it was the first

01:23:29.200 --> 01:23:34.120
[Guest]: time I was away from home it was in the East Coast where nine months of winter

01:23:34.120 --> 01:23:40.560
[Guest]: literally getting dark at 3 o'clock you did need that comforting situation you

01:23:40.560 --> 01:23:45.080
[Guest]: know to replicate like a feeling of home and that's when I actually started

01:23:45.080 --> 01:23:50.600
[Amit Varma]: cooking. So you know that whole journey is very fascinating and different

